            <h1>Our Conservation Projects</h1>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="page-content">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="content-block">
                <h2>Reforestation Initiative</h2>
                <p>Our reforestation program focuses on restoring the critical watershed areas of the Rwenzori Mountains. We work with local communities to plant native tree species that are essential for maintaining the mountain ecosystem.</p>
                
                <div class="image-gallery">
                    <div class="gallery-item">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1504814532849-cff240bbc503?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80" alt="Tree planting">
                    </div>
                    <div class="gallery-item">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1504814532849-cff240bbc503?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80" alt="Community involvement">
                    </div>
                    <div class="gallery-item">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1504814532849-cff240bbc503?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80" alt="Reforested area">
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <h3>Program Highlights</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Native Species:</strong> Planting indigenous trees that support local wildlife</li>
                    <li><strong>Community Nurseries:</strong> Establishing 12 community-run tree nurseries</li>
                    <li><strong>Watershed Protection:</strong> Focusing on critical river source areas</li>
                    <li><strong>Carbon Sequestration:</strong> Each tree absorbs approximately 22 kg of CO₂ annually</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="content-block">
                <h2>Wildlife Conservation</h2>
                <p>Protecting the unique biodiversity of the Rwenzori Mountains is central to our mission. Our wildlife conservation programs focus on preserving habitat and reducing human-wildlife conflict.</p>
                
                <div class="image-gallery">
                    <div class="gallery-item">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1546182990-dffeafbe841d?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80" alt="Wildlife">
                    </div>
                    <div class="gallery-item">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1546182990-dffeafbe841d?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80" alt="Elephant">
                    </div>
                    <div class="gallery-item">
                        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1546182990-dffeafbe841d?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80" alt="Chimpanzee">
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <h3>Key Initiatives</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Beehive Fences:</strong> Protecting farms from elephants without harm</li>
                    <li><strong>Anti-Poaching Patrols:</strong> Deploying rangers to protect endangered species</li>
                    <li><strong>Wildlife Corridors:</strong> Creating safe passages for animal movement</li>
                    <li><strong>Camera Trapping:</strong> Monitoring wildlife populations and behavior</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            
            <div class="content-block">
                <h2>Our Team</h2>
                <p>Our conservation efforts are led by a diverse team of ecologists, community organizers, and local experts dedicated to preserving the Rwenzori Mountains.</p>
                
                <div class="team-grid">
                    <div class="team-member">
                        <div class="team-photo">
                            <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1507003211169-0a1dd7228f2d?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80" alt="Dr. Amina Nalwoga">
                        </div>
                        <h3>Dr. Amina Nalwoga</h3>
                        <p>Lead Ecologist</p>
                        <p>PhD in Conservation Biology with 15 years of experience in mountain ecosystems</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="team-member">
                        <div class="team-photo">
